extendedInfo.description: Join us in San Antonio for practical advice and in-depth discussion of the issues and problems confronting family law practitioners today. We've also carefully put together an outstanding faculty of leading practitioners and highly-regarded judges to get you quickly and completely up to date on the latest case law, legislation, emerging trends & issues, and breaking developments.  Full-day tracks will cover SAPCR and Property/Divorce as well as the Child Abuse & Neglect Workshop. Half-day tracks cover Valuation of Property and Characterization & Tracing, Appellate, Technology and Collaborative Law  Earn up to 22.5 MCLE hours and up to 7.75 hours of ethics[State Bar], [TBCLE],[Family Law], [Marriott Rivercenter], [2011], [San Antonio], [CLE], [conference]
